{
  "texts": [
    "Pyramidal neurons:",
    "Neurons exhibit a distinctive cellular structure, featuring apical and basal dendritic trees, as well as a pyramidal-shaped soma (Spruston, 2008).",
    "RandomForest: machine learning algorithm used for classification and regression, where the result is generated from the combination of multiple decision trees.",
    "Each decision tree is an independent model that divides the data into subsets based on a sequence of rules for data features (Belgiu and Drȃguţ, 2016).",
    "Regional homogeneity (ReHo): concept and analysis technique to measure the similarity or coherence of the blood oxygen level-dependent (BOLD) signal within a specific brain region or voxel (Xu et al., 2019)."
  ]
}